article.headline: Idaho St. 68, Sacramento St. 67
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Kenny McGowen's four-point play with 8 seconds remaining gave Idaho State a come-from-behind 68-67 win over Sacramento State Saturday night. Sacramento State led 54-32 with just over 10 minutes left, and 64-54 with 1:58 to go. McGowen, who finished with 19 points, hit a 3-pointer to start the rally. Abner Moreira, who had 10 rebounds, tipped in McGowen's miss to get Idaho State within 66-64. Heath Hoffman made a free throw for Sacramento State with 12 seconds left, but McGowen made a 3 and was fouled in the process. He made the free throw to put the Bengals ahead for just the second time all night. The first lead was at 9-8. Chase Grabau led Idaho State (4-13, 2/3 Big Sky) with 20 points. Konner Veteto had 25 points for the Hornets (5-11, 0-5).
